content.description: A thin crack that runs up the edge of an arete leading to the top of the Second Cliff Band Above the Mining Road.
content.location: The arete crack can be found just left and below an incipient crack running over a roof near the center of the cliff. Rig natural anchors on top and walk off right (west).

content.description: "Queen Jane" is a thin crack going up the inside of a dihedral on the left-hand side of the Second Cliff Band Above the Mining Road. It starts out tips and opens up into wide hands near the top. Where the crack ends traverse up and right to a belay stance next to some roofs.
content.protection: 1/2" to 4 inches. QJ goes through a full range of sizes from tips to big hands.
content.location: On the left edge of the Second Cliff Above the Mining Road.

content.description: The route begins with a 5.10b crack crux below a small tower. After the traversing left over the tower, climb a 5.10c crack leading up into a right-facing dihedral that takes you to the summit of the cliff band.
content.protection: Regular rack to 3.5". Arrange natural anchors in the rubble on top.
content.location: A good landmark for finding the start of "Mister Catastrophe" is an obvious 5.10 hand crack leading to a big ledge. "Mister Catastrophe" starts just up and left of the hand crack.
